{meta: title Dear Lord Don't Let Go Of My Hand}
{meta: artist Jimmie Davis}
{meta: writer Marshall Pack and Jimmie Davis}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]When my soul is dark with grief
Give my heart God's blessed peace
And dear [G7]Lord don't let go of my [C]hand
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
When my friends have passed me by
In my loneliness I cry
Then dear [G7]Lord don't let go of my [C]hand
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
Oh dear Lord don't let [G7]go of my [C]hand
I'll be true just as [D7]long as I [G7]can
And when I [C]stumble and fall
Oh dear [F]God please give me [C]hope
And dear Lord don't let [G7]go of my [C]hand
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
When trials come on every hand
And I cannot understand
Oh dear [G7]Lord don't let go of my [C]hand
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
When it comes my time to die
And I hear my loved ones cry
Then dear [G7]Lord don't let go of my [C]hand
{end_of_verse}

